description.narrative: Key results in early childhood education include a further increase in the coverage of the pre-primary year reaching 88% in 2019. UNICEF supported the national roll-out of the new pre-primary curriculum in the classrooms for the school year 2019-2020 and the launch of a new bachelor's degree for early childhood educators. New quality standards for early childhood education services were finalized in partnership with three ministries and the private sector and are currently being modelled in three reference centres with a focus on vulnerable children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/01/2020
